<TEXT>
mikhail baryshnikov has done more than touch up 
the paint on swan lake he has rethought it and the 
centerpiece of the american ballet theater production that opened 
at the metropolitan opera on monday night is the ultraromantic duet 
in act 2 
swan lake never was for feminists but this 15 million 
production first danced by the company in december in costa mesa 
calif is even more romantic than most 
the swan queen danced by susan jaffe on monday night as well as 
in the california premiere is shy at the beginning of her pas de 
deux with ross stretton the prince who is entranced by her as 
they dance she clearly falls in love begins to trust him becomes 
happy poised and feminine in general expands to her potential 
through loving a man 
one reason this works so clearly is that the music in the latter 
part of the pas de deux is slowed allowing the two performers to 
spin out their dance movements musically another reason is that 
throughout the ballet miss jaffe is able to act with body language 
as well as dance superbly 
her arms ripple in the approved way of a swan queen but with 
miss jaffe one notices the rest of her body as well when she 
appears in act 3 as the evil magician rothbarts daughter to 
trick the prince she is as glittering as a diamond but not as 
hard she maintains some of the softness she has as the swan queen 
baryshnikov chooses to have her wear white with sequins it 
works but we think a traditional black swan costume works 
better 
act 1 often something of a bore as people walk and stand 
around has been filled with enjoyable dancing by baryshnikov the 
men were giving real dancing and looked good we enjoyed the first 
acts pas de trois by deirdre carberry christina fagundes and john 
gardner the corps de ballet of swans in later acts also was fine 
the staging throughout stressed that swan lake is theater 
not just dancing for that reason the least interesting part is 
baryshnikovs act 4 dances for the swans much of it looks like 
unorganized swooping around for some reason six of them now are 
in black and four of those dance with four in white interest picks 
up when the swan queen now looking wounded but loving and 
forgiving and the prince come in 
rothbart danced by michael owen in a mask with a beaked face 
topped by tall feathers comes in loses his power in the face of 
true love and has a neat brief death scene his home tower isnt 
visible so nothing crumbles the lovers walk into the lake and 
ascend into heaven as the swans walk around becoming women the 
latter an interesting new touch 
baryshnikovs choreography is added to that of marius petipa and 
lev ivanov jack everly conducted 
</TEXT>
