<TEXT>
a tiny barefoot 3yearold girl carries her even 
smaller sister on her back as she wanders onto a stage in 
madagascar to stand near the pope from faraway rome 
a french missionary in malawi springs from the crowd and breaks 
into a spontaneous african celebration dance at the foot of the 
altar waving his arms back and forth over his head 
a young beggar boy tugs at the robes of a bishop and pleads for 
a handout during a stadium youth rally in zambia 
these were some of the faces of africa that pope john paul ii 
glimpsed during his fifth trip to the continent 
the nineday tour which ended saturday provided the pope with 
the picture of an africa that suffers from some of the worst 
poverty in the world but bursts with a richness of tradition and 
faith 
everywhere he went from dusty airfields to regal presidential 
palaces john paul found a christianity that wont sit still even 
at masses usually solemn ceremonies the pope was surrounded by 
colorful dancers singers and tribal drummers 
the beautiful ceremonies and the wonderful spirit of 
celebration that accompanied them are special memories for me he 
said in his farewell speach in blantyre malawi i will treasure 
them 
some memorable moments from john pauls 41st foreign pilgrimage 
in antsiranana on the northern tip of the impoverished island 
of madagascar a french missionary nun brings an abandoned 
11monthold baby girl to receive the popes blessing at an 
openair mass angelicas mother is believed to be a prostitute 
at the end of the service the child is carried to the steps of 
the altar by the girls foster mother who kneels at the pontiffs 
feet the pope takes angelica in his arms kisses her on the 
forehead and gives her his blessing 
we wanted the popes benediction to give hope to all abandoned 
children says jeanine couve the french nun who runs an 
orphanage 
in antananarivo the capital of madagascar the pope is 
getting ready to address tens of thousands of youths in a soccer 
stadium when the 3yearold girl with her 1yearold sister on her 
back wanders out of the dancing crowd climbs the steps of the 
stage and walks over to where john paul is sitting 
the pope smiling broadly embraces both of them and gives them 
rosaries the girl stands next to the pope for a few minutes before 
slipping back into the crowd 
in lusaka zambia the pope mixes with the youths in the 
independence stadium and briefly joins them in swaying to the 
lilting african beat 
your desire to celebrate in song and dance today shows the 
churchs desire to celebrate and share the message of christs love 
with the whole world he says 
the women flight attendants on an air malawi flight from 
blantyre to lilongwe fall to their knees in the aisle to serve the 
pope a gesture that not only shows respect but also is in keeping 
with womens traditional subservience to men in malawi 
in a striking sign of the order and discipline in the former 
british colony of malawi the tens of thousands of people lining 
the papal motorcade route in blantyre stand in a perfect nearly 
motionless line for miles without a single barrier or armed 
policeman to hold them back 
malawis presidentforlife hastings kamuzu banda orchestrated 
some of the most unusual scenes of the popes tour often upstaging 
his guest 
at the welcoming ceremony at the blantyre airport banda 
wearing a homburg carrying an elephant hair fly wisk and 
surrounded by his personal cadre of hundreds of brightly costumed 
women dancers joked with the pope and pulled him up from his chair 
for a long embrace 
banda who is believed to be in his early 90s took center stage 
again at a mass the following day with the pope waiting in a hall 
nearby banda and his official hostess mama c tamanda 
kadzamira arrived 10 minutes late in a black mercedes limousine 
encircled by his dancers and waving his fly wisk out the window 
the pope doesnt take these things too seriously said 
vatican spokesman joaquin navarro he understands the need to 
understand and adapt to local cultures 
