it dramatically reduced the amount of seed produced said 
harley j otto executive vice president of the minnesota crop 
improvement association which certifies seed for certain 
standards minnesota leads the nation in the number of acres of 
certified seed 
the more popular better producing seeds are in short 
supply he said 
last summers drought slashed yields of corn and soybean seed by 
as much as 35 percent 
the small crop forced seed producers such as northrup king co 
and cargill inc to deplete reserves and call upon winter 
production facilities more than two decades had passed since 
northrup was forced to rely on winter facilities in texas and 
argentina the company said 
although farmers got all the corn seed they needed not all got 
the topofthe line seed they wanted 
they got good hybrids but if they had a choice they probably 
would have chosen a different one said don jacoby northrups 
vice president of agriproducts sales 
we did not have enough of our topline hybrids for the central 
and southern corn belt we had to ration them out said bruce 
priebe president of cargill hybrid seeds 
and if the drought continues seed producers say some farmers 
may be lucky to get quality seed at all for the 1990 growing season 
if we have another drought this year its going to affect our 
whole industry very severely said ag laos vice president of 
northrups us agriproducts group it would be a major 
catastrophe for the industry and for agriculture here in the us 
david l thomas northrups executive marketing director said 
if the drought repeats itself last years dry spell will seem like 
playtime in comparison 
itll just be a disaster he said 
jack riopelle owner of the 850acre riopelle seed farm in the 
northwest minnesota town of argyle agreed 
this year will be a little tighter than it usually is said 
riopelle who lost onefourth of his wheat barely soybean and pea 
seed crop to last years dryness well be able to survive but 
its going to be a pinch if we have another drought a person can 
hold out only for so long 
