<DOCNO> AP890508-0210 </DOCNO>
<TEXT>
 
manila philippines ap here are major dates in the 20year 
communist insurgency in the philippines 
dec 26 1968 leftist intellectuals and peasant militants led 
by prof jose maria sison break away from the largely defunct 
promoscow communist organization and establish the maoist 
communist party of the philippines 
march 29 1969 the new party organizes the new peoples army 
and launch a peoples war to establish a communist state 
sept 22 1972 president ferdinand marcos citing a communist 
threat declares martial law and arrests thousands of opponents 
nov 10 1977 sison is arrested in la union province but the 
insurgency continues to grow because of public opposition to marcos 
feb 25 1986 marcos is overthrown in a popular uprising 
triggered by a military mutiny marcos flees into exile in hawaii 
and corazon aquino succeeds him as president 
march 5 1986 mrs aquino releases hundreds of political 
prisoners including sison and other party leaders 
sept 30 1986 party chairman rudolfo salas is arrested outside 
a government hospital in manila and is charged with rebellion and 
subversion 
dec 10 1986 the government and the partydominated national 
democratic front sign a 60day nationwide ceasefire and begin 
peace talks 
jan 22 1987 peace talks collapse after the government rejects 
powersharing and after police kill at least 13 protesters during a 
march for land reform in manila 
feb 8 1987 ceasefire expires and fighting resumes 
oct 28 1987 rebels assassinate three americans and a filipino 
of us descent outside the usrun clark air base it is the 
first time americans have been targeted during the insurgency 
march 29 1988 police arrest key members of the central 
committee including party secretarygeneral rafael baylosis and 
military commander romulo kintanar government claims rebellion 
suffers major blow 
nov 12 1988 kintanar and his wife escape from a manila 
stockade kintanar claims he has resumed post as chief of staff of 
the new peoples army 
april 21 1989 col james n rowe of the joint us military 
advisory group is assassinated a rebel statement says he was slain 
because of american interference in the philippines 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

