gorillas in the mist mca home video vhsbeta 8995 
rated pg13 
 
dian fossey was a driven committed woman a woman who gave up 
the comforts and safety of home her love life and her appendix to 
live with gorillas in central africa 
but she crossed that fine line between commitment and obsession 
between a illusion and reality and paid for the voyage with her 
life 
gorillas in the mist attempts to examine the life of the 
anthropologist who dedicated her life to saving an endangered 
population of gorillas in rwanda she fought poachers government 
officials animal traders and her own colleagues 
sigourney weaver stars as fossey but her performance is more a 
character study for a drama class than a finished product she 
stumbles through an array of emotions from joy to enthusiasm to 
wonder to rage but simply doesnt have the depth to be convincing 
fossey was a complex unconventional woman in weaver we see only 
a silly shrill 
but the gorillas are cute and far more interesting than the 
star 
bryan brown puts in an admirable performance as a national 
geographic photographer and fosseys sometime lover there also are 
good support jobs by john miluwi as fosseys house man and tracker 
and julie harris as a white local who befriends the anthropologist 
they overpower weaver who seems an amateur out of her league 
despite an academy nomination for the role 
if you can suffer through sigourney weavers acting youll 
enjoy the stunning vistas and beautiful photography of gorillas 
in the mist 
