the album opener talent show is extremely effective in 
capturing the mood of anticipation that comes with a rock show the 
jaunty asking me lies which talks about a mexican bar mitzvah 
and ill be you are also strong 
but songs such as back to back and well inherit the 
earth sound tentative and selfconscious its not the style 
changes its just a lack of strong material and the replacements 
arent adept enough at covering up the lost feeling that comes when 
theyre working on a subpar composition 
despite the occasional flashes dont tell a soul is flat a 
workmanlike album from a band that probably has better days ahead 
by david bauder associated press writer 
</TEXT>
