court order preventing a partnership of amway corp and minneapolis 
investor irwin jacobs from acquiring more avon stock 
the suit filed in us district court in new york accused 
amway and jacobs of violating disclosure requirements of federal 
securities laws in their acquisition of avon stock avon said in a 
statement 
the suit asked that amway and jacobs be ordered to sell the avon 
stock they already have purchased the new yorkbased cosmetics and 
household products company said 
were not familiar with it amway spokeswoman kim bruyn said 
monday afternoon we havent seen it and therefore we have no 
comment 
earlier monday amway cofounder jay van andel said the ada 
michbased company had nt decided whether to pursue acquisition of 
avon its larger rival in the direct selling business 
amway a large direct seller of personal and home products has 
purchased more than 10 percent of avon common stock in the past 
month in partnership with jacobs a wellknown takeover strategist 
van andel told the grand rapids mich economic club that a 
takeover would have to benefit both companies 
he compared amways position to that of a diver who walks out on 
the diving board and has to decide whether to make a swan dive 
or a belly flop we havent made that decision yet were still 
on the board looking around 
if we were to decide to make the plunge the plunge would 
have to be good for amway as a company and avon as a company van 
andel said 
the statement released by avon described amway as a 
controversial purveyor of a pyramidal direct marketing scheme that 
has never made a major acquisition 
it also described jacobs as a wellknown raider who has not 
completed an acquisition for many years or any acquisition for 
significantly more than 500 million 
